c: 35
v: 8
t: "Are those whose evil-doing is made so appealing to them that they deem it good ňĻlike those who are rightly guidedňļ? ňĻIt isňļ certainly God ňĻWhoňļ leaves to stray whoever He wills, and guides whoever He wills. So do not grieve yourself to death over them ňĻO Prophetňļ. Surely God is All-Knowing of what they do"